      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "FINAL DEADLINE NZ (2) was too good here first-up, coming from a 10m handicap and racing parked before drawing away to score by more than 8m. That was his first outing since seconds in both the Chariots of Fire and Light Horse Free For All at the autumn carnival in Sydney. Has trialled since the fresh effort so should have come on. The low draw will see him hard to stop. FATE AWAITS (8) kicked off his campaign with back-to-back wins before working and clocking in third as a hot favourite last start. Beat Final Deadline at the trials since and draws for a trail so could bounce back. JUNGLE DRAGON (5) was runner-up to Final Deadline when fresh then progressed for a dominant win here last week. That took his record at this distance to two from two. Major player. COOL AND CLASSY (7) cops a wide draw for her return to Brisbane but she is a smart mare with an impressive strike rate here. Stablemate RUBY RULES (10) also cops a tricky draw but she has come back in good order so include.",
